messages.message: Should the cleaning output of a `No value found` value be `Cleaning failed`? To me `Cleaning failed` seems like something went wrong and it's an error, when there's actually no value to be cleaned. Especially with these prebuilt cleaning options I feel like we should handle these better
In human review you can't interrogate the result like you can in the config, so its even more problematic
Yeah I agree that this gives the wrong impression (even though it might technically be true)
We don’t have a way to fix this for Human Review since whether or not you have a cleaning line, the returned result will be the same (I assume either `ERROR` or `No value found`) cc @Udit

On the Build side, we could check whether the extraction step has `No value found` -> if so, show the same for the cleaning lines

@danny.lan was there a particular reason that we didn’t do this previously?

Yah, this should just show No value found. What is the returned value in the endpoint? If that says "Cleaning failed.", that should be what is fixed. Human review should just show "No value found" which is what the endpoint ideally returns.
This is what Build and App Run return respectively
`Cleaning failed` is a catch-all that we use, now what we can differentiate error vs no value, I can update this to show a different message if there is no value
